b"File Under: Autumn Serenity. :smiling_face_with_heart-eyes::maple_leaf: The first and largest royal palace built during the Joseon Dynasty, the Gyeongbokgung Palace in Seoul is often considered the most beautiful, too! The Hyangwonjeong Pavilion (pictured here) is a two-story building located on a small manmade island in the middle of one of the palace's ponds. It was built by King Gojong in 1873! #ExpediaPic
:round_pushpin:Seoul, South Korea
